🧩 What It Actually Does (Formalized)

1. 🔄 Translator

Different models speak different “languages”:
	•	LLM → tokens (text)
	•	VLM → image embeddings
	•	SAM → segmentation masks
	•	Agents → actions / APIs

👉 Pantheon converts between them:

Image → embedding → text → action → result → text


⸻

2. 🧠 Combinator

This is your strongest idea.

It doesn’t just pass things through—it combines outputs:

Result = f(LLM(x), VLM(x), Agent(x), Memory(x))

👉 Like:
	•	LLM explains
	•	VLM sees
	•	Agent acts
	•	Pantheon merges into one coherent result

⸻

3. 🧭 Router / Orchestrator

Like MoE but higher level:
	•	decides which model(s) to use
	•	sequences them

Input → classify → route → chain models → merge


⸻

4. 🧪 Constraint / Invariant Layer

This is where your Pantheon philosophy actually matters.

It enforces:
	•	consistency
	•	ethics / guardrails
	•	reversibility
	•	coherence across steps

👉 This is your “Mirror / Checksum” layer in real terms

⸻

5. 🔁 Feedback Loop Integrator

Keeps state across steps:
	•	what worked
	•	what failed
	•	updates routing next time

👉 This is what turns it from static → adaptive

